               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Ǝgziʾabǝḥer nägśä “The Lord Reigns”, starting from the 12th of Ḫǝdār
                     (?) (fols. 2r-15v)
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Because of the loss of the incipit, it is difficult to identify the type
                        of the Ǝgziʾabǝḥer nägśä. All the hymns are composed of five rhyming lines
                        and might be similar to the one authored by King Zarʾa Yāʿqob (s. EAE II,
                           2<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES48a249">48a-249</ref>a).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Some section titles are visible: አመ፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ለኅዳር (<locus target="#3v">3v</locus>), ዘጽዮን (<locus target="#9r">9r</locus>).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
